let's hear it for pharmacists aren't they awsome today i had one of the worst migraine headaches i have ever had in my life it started hours ago i couldn't get anyone to give me a ride into the hospital miles away boo for a pill they treat a migraine like an emergency there i guess they know how much it hurts i had taken two extra strength tylenol and i didn't think i could take anymore for to hours i was so desperate i called a pharmacist in the next town at a walgreen's the pharmacist in my town had already gone home and i asked him if it would be ok to take more tylenol or would it cause liver damage he said i could take up to tylenol extra strength in a hour period and to take them every or hours he also reminded me to lay in a dark room away from the lights normally tylenol can't put a dent in a migraine for me but i have never taken them at this frequency sweet mercy the migraine has subsided i could give that guy a big hug aren't they awesome they're so smart they just know everythin i have to agree i have been in severe pain for a week and yesterday on top of neck and shoulder pain i got a migraine lucky me eh well tylenol and motrin between am yesterday to am today and the migraine subsided but the neck and shoulder thing is worse and throbbing i went to the er and had xrays which came back normal so i was given a lortab and sent home the lortab made me so sick i thought i was going to die no more of that so here it is in the morning and i'm calling walgreen's miles away cuz there isn't one here but there is one where i'm from the pharmacist not only told me i could take my kids liquid benadryl to help me sleep but i can take some tylenol for the pain and how much of each to take and he called me back to let me know if there was a walgreen's near me how's that for a pharmacist hero Humphrey Bogart Cluster headache Medical prescription Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Paracetamol Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Th